19
00:00:00,780 --> 00:00:02,330
Previously on Z Nation.

20
00:00:02,330 --> 00:00:03,590
Those are zombie bites.

21
00:00:03,770 --> 00:00:04,600
Eight of them.

22
00:00:04,620 --> 00:00:06,930
You're looking at the only human known to have survived

23
00:00:06,930 --> 00:00:08,060
being bitten by a zombie.

24
00:00:08,060 --> 00:00:10,150
If we can get him to the lab in California

25
00:00:10,150 --> 00:00:12,840
they can use his blood and make more of the vaccine.

26
00:00:13,050 --> 00:00:14,060
Is that what I think?!

27
00:00:14,060 --> 00:00:15,220
They ain't sharks!

28
00:00:15,220 --> 00:00:16,240
You still think about him?

29
00:00:16,360 --> 00:00:17,300
Antoine?

30
00:00:17,300 --> 00:00:18,320
I try not to.

31
00:00:18,390 --> 00:00:19,120
Antoine?

32
00:00:20,050 --> 00:00:20,930
Is that him?

33
00:00:21,080 --> 00:00:21,820
No.

34
00:00:22,530 --> 00:00:25,010
Even if I never know for sure what happened to Antoine

35
00:00:25,150 --> 00:00:28,100
I'm okay with being here now with you.

36
00:00:28,270 --> 00:00:29,650
I'm good with that too.

37
00:00:38,750 --> 00:00:40,230
This is a national emergency.

38
00:00:40,230 --> 00:00:41,480
I've decided to catalog

39
00:00:41,480 --> 00:00:44,020
all the theories about where the Z virus came from.

40
00:00:44,290 --> 00:00:45,540
There's more than a few.

41
00:00:45,720 --> 00:00:48,560
Is it what the Zoroastrians would call Frashokereti?

42
00:00:48,720 --> 00:00:51,530
Or are we contaminated with Amazon brain rot?

43
00:00:51,920 --> 00:00:54,390
Or maybe we passed through the tail of a comet

44
00:00:54,390 --> 00:00:56,150
that sprinkled the earth with zombie dust.

45
00:00:57,060 --> 00:00:59,520
Or was it a defense department weaponized virus

46
00:00:59,520 --> 00:01:00,580
that escaped the lab?

47
00:01:01,310 --> 00:01:02,250
Or how about

48
00:01:02,450 --> 00:01:03,740
self fulfilling prophecy.

49
00:01:03,940 --> 00:01:06,740
Public fascination with all things zombie just

50
00:01:06,880 --> 00:01:08,550
willed it into existence.

51
00:01:09,950 --> 00:01:12,630
As things went south the theories got weirder.

52
00:01:13,070 --> 00:01:15,680
Good times for religions with an end of the world scenario.

53
00:01:15,680 --> 00:01:16,960
The crazier the better.

54
00:01:17,520 --> 00:01:19,540
The Apocalypse business was booming.

55
00:01:19,540 --> 00:01:21,720
At least while there still was business to boom.

57
00:01:22,590 --> 00:01:24,480
It reminds me of a poem by Yeats.

58
00:01:25,300 --> 00:01:28,570
"And what rough beast, its hour come round at last,

59
00:01:28,760 --> 00:01:30,830
slouches toward Bethlehem to be born?"

60
00:01:31,030 --> 00:01:32,370
There is no cure.

61
00:01:33,840 --> 00:01:35,740
What rough beast indeed.

63
00:01:39,340 --> 00:01:43,360
Father, we ask that watch over our brothers and sisters

64
00:01:43,850 --> 00:01:46,920
as they leave our congregation for a greater journey.

65
00:01:47,260 --> 00:01:48,240
Amen.

66
00:01:48,600 --> 00:01:51,420
And although we will not see them again in this life,

67
00:01:51,940 --> 00:01:54,480
they will live on through their sacrifice.

68
00:01:55,620 --> 00:01:57,240
Now I ask you all to rise.

69
00:01:58,190 --> 00:01:59,850
Brother Eli, Brother Matthew,

70
00:02:00,420 --> 00:02:01,960
please help with the Resurrected

71
00:02:10,780 --> 00:02:11,900
Let us pray.

72
00:02:12,780 --> 00:02:15,140
For today is a day of joy.

74
00:02:17,370 --> 00:02:20,020
I ask now for the anointed to please step forward.

75
00:02:24,010 --> 00:02:25,950
These brothers and sisters

76
00:02:26,490 --> 00:02:29,250
will soon know the true meaning of peace

77
00:02:29,890 --> 00:02:33,360
that only belief and resurrection can bring.

78
00:02:37,350 --> 00:02:39,250
May these keep you safe on your journey

79
00:02:41,710 --> 00:02:45,160
and serve as the instrument of your salvation.

80
00:02:46,130 --> 00:02:47,520
I envy you, brothers.

81
00:02:48,090 --> 00:02:48,990
Sister.

82
00:02:59,060 --> 00:03:00,540
Let us ring the bell

83
00:03:00,770 --> 00:03:03,950
and joyously call out for more of the resurrected

84
00:03:03,950 --> 00:03:05,460
to join our flock.

85
00:03:09,830 --> 00:03:10,970
Brother Eli.

86
00:03:11,170 --> 00:03:12,240
Brother Matthew.

87
00:03:12,490 --> 00:03:13,900
Please prepare to greet them.

88
00:03:47,240 --> 00:03:48,380
No Zs in sight.

89
00:03:49,710 --> 00:03:52,420
Anybody else worried about Mr. Sunshine out there?

90
00:03:52,510 --> 00:03:53,090
I know.

91
00:03:53,090 --> 00:03:54,210
He's looking worse.

92
00:03:54,500 --> 00:03:56,460
Yeah, he was pretty creepy to start with.

93
00:03:56,580 --> 00:03:58,100
Come on, guys. Give him a break.

94
00:03:59,060 --> 00:04:01,240
It's the Apocalypse. None of us look our best.

95
00:04:02,100 --> 00:04:03,910
It's like one long bad hair day.

96
00:04:04,200 --> 00:04:06,070
Speaking of hair, what's with all the bald patches?

97
00:04:06,260 --> 00:04:08,170
Maybe that vaccine is like zombie chemo.

98
00:04:08,250 --> 00:04:09,870
Or maybe that vaccine isn't working.

99
00:04:24,840 --> 00:04:25,960
What do you think, Doc?

100
00:04:26,530 --> 00:04:28,580
I've seen Zs look better than him.

101
00:04:30,200 --> 00:04:31,700
Will he make it to California?

102
00:04:32,170 --> 00:04:33,340
If we haul ass.

103
00:04:33,660 --> 00:04:36,360
If he goes zombie, we might have to put him down.

104
00:04:36,360 --> 00:04:37,490
Dibs on piking him.

105
00:04:38,480 --> 00:04:41,150
If he turns, piking him's the least of our problems.

106
00:04:47,930 --> 00:04:48,730
What?

107
00:04:49,720 --> 00:04:51,510
Pit stop's over. Let's get moving.

108
00:04:52,260 --> 00:04:54,040
I have a ginormous bladder.

109
00:04:54,350 --> 00:04:55,320
Sue me.

110
00:04:58,730 --> 00:05:02,650
Man, I sure could use some of them Kansas City barbecue ribs about now.

111
00:05:02,830 --> 00:05:05,820
How bout you, darlin'. You're a big rib eater, aren't you?

112
00:05:06,150 --> 00:05:09,310
You know I was almost starting to feel sorry for you.

113
00:05:11,170 --> 00:05:13,440
You look pretty happy for someone who hasn't eaten

114
00:05:13,440 --> 00:05:14,430
in two days.

115
00:05:15,220 --> 00:05:15,970
Could be worse.

116
00:05:16,190 --> 00:05:17,010
Really?

117
00:05:17,280 --> 00:05:18,390
We're still alive, aren't we?

118
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:22,870
You were always a glass half full kinda guy.

119
00:05:23,370 --> 00:05:24,670
It's what I love about you.

120
00:05:26,440 --> 00:05:27,810
Actually I'm looking forward to getting some food

121
00:05:27,810 --> 00:05:29,790
and a hot shower at Provincetown.

122
00:05:29,790 --> 00:05:30,840
Well don't get your hopes up.

123
00:05:30,840 --> 00:05:32,770
We don't even know if this place still exists.

124
00:05:32,770 --> 00:05:35,880
Hammond had it marked on his map as a resupply place.

125
00:05:35,880 --> 00:05:38,340
And if his contact there is the same Major Williams

126
00:05:38,340 --> 00:05:39,830
from my National Guard days,

127
00:05:39,830 --> 00:05:41,070
we might actually get some help.

128
00:05:41,070 --> 00:05:43,430
So we're relying on the map of a dead guy?

129
00:05:43,430 --> 00:05:44,740
In case you forgot

130
00:05:44,740 --> 00:05:48,410
that dead guy was a hero who died protecting you.

131
00:05:48,450 --> 00:05:50,930
Just because he's dead doesn't make him a hero.

132
00:05:51,670 --> 00:05:53,570
Well I hope Provincetown does exist

133
00:05:53,570 --> 00:05:56,170
because we're out of just about everything but hope.

134
00:06:27,400 --> 00:06:29,170
One thousand five hundred and fifty four.

136
00:06:46,550 --> 00:06:49,040
Surrender all weapons? Are they serious?

137
00:06:49,150 --> 00:06:50,050
Looks like.

138
00:06:51,100 --> 00:06:52,210
What do you wanna do?

139
00:06:53,660 --> 00:06:55,200
Their town, their rules.

140
00:06:55,860 --> 00:06:57,660
Looks like we don't have much of a choice.

141
00:07:08,030 --> 00:07:11,170
Stop right there! This is a private compound.

142
00:07:11,480 --> 00:07:13,230
I'm gonna have to ask you to turn around

143
00:07:13,230 --> 00:07:14,710
and go back the way you came.

144
00:07:20,490 --> 00:07:21,930
I'm looking for Major Wiliams.

145
00:07:22,840 --> 00:07:24,120
Joe Williams.

146
00:07:24,120 --> 00:07:24,960
And who are you?

147
00:07:25,360 --> 00:07:26,660
I'm Sergeant Charles Garnett,

148
00:07:26,660 --> 00:07:27,960
Georgia National Guard.

149
00:07:29,730 --> 00:07:32,020
We've knowm each other going back pre-z.

150
00:07:37,550 --> 00:07:40,020
Wait there. Your crew stays in the truck.

151
00:07:40,130 --> 00:07:42,420
They try to get out or we see a weapon,

152
00:07:42,420 --> 00:07:43,140
we'll fire.

153
00:07:45,680 --> 00:07:47,060
Easy everyone.

154
00:07:47,060 --> 00:07:48,830
Charlie's got it under control.

155
00:07:48,830 --> 00:07:50,700
So you're calling him Charlie now?

156
00:07:50,900 --> 00:07:53,420
Yeah, and I'm gonna start calling you my bitch

157
00:07:53,420 --> 00:07:54,860
if you don't shut up.

158
00:08:01,650 --> 00:08:04,760
Well holy shit.

159
00:08:06,490 --> 00:08:08,670
It's the ghost of Charlie Garnett.

160
00:08:09,010 --> 00:08:12,400
Never expected to see you again. At least not alive.

161
00:08:12,500 --> 00:08:15,660
Hey, Joe. Didn't expect to see you again either.

162
00:08:16,690 --> 00:08:18,430
Looks like we're both still standing.

163
00:08:18,840 --> 00:08:19,860
Looks like.

164
00:08:20,460 --> 00:08:21,520
Last time I saw you,

165
00:08:21,520 --> 00:08:24,180
you were pulling my ass out of a ditch full of Zs.

166
00:08:24,520 --> 00:08:25,880
Just returning the favor.

167
00:08:26,880 --> 00:08:28,610
How many Zs we kill that day?

168
00:08:30,070 --> 00:08:31,100
Not enough.

169
00:08:33,100 --> 00:08:33,950
Do you mind?

170
00:08:36,350 --> 00:08:37,380
Stand down.

171
00:08:39,100 --> 00:08:41,630
You're the first person I've seen from before.

172
00:08:42,950 --> 00:08:44,750
How the hell you end up here?

173
00:08:45,440 --> 00:08:47,180
I'm actually on a mission for the government,

174
00:08:47,210 --> 00:08:48,390
if you can believe that.

175
00:08:49,570 --> 00:08:50,990
If it was anybody but you,

176
00:08:51,310 --> 00:08:52,160
I wouldn't.

177
00:08:52,450 --> 00:08:55,110
We've come from New York. Haven't eaten in a few days.

178
00:08:56,080 --> 00:08:57,130
New York?

179
00:08:57,590 --> 00:08:58,220
Haven't seen anyone

180
00:08:58,220 --> 00:09:00,590
east of the Mississippi for over a year.

181
00:09:00,770 --> 00:09:01,690
How many of you are there?

182
00:09:01,820 --> 00:09:03,690
Eight. Including a doctor.

183
00:09:04,570 --> 00:09:05,750
Real doctor?

184
00:09:06,050 --> 00:09:06,900
Sort of.

185
00:09:07,080 --> 00:09:08,610
He's watched a lot of E.R.

186
00:09:11,410 --> 00:09:12,220
All right.

187
00:09:13,190 --> 00:09:16,010
Come inside and tell me your story. We'll get you some food.

188
00:09:16,300 --> 00:09:18,090
But the truck stays outside.

189
00:09:19,330 --> 00:09:20,200
Let them in.

190
00:09:20,620 --> 00:09:23,050
And of course you'll have to check your weapons.

191
00:09:27,380 --> 00:09:28,750
Just make sure we get these back.

192
00:09:32,260 --> 00:09:34,310
Why is this not making me feel any safer?

193
00:09:35,560 --> 00:09:37,170
Looks like it's seen a little action.

194
00:09:38,400 --> 00:09:39,660
Ex prison guard?

195
00:09:39,750 --> 00:09:40,610
TSA.

196
00:09:43,020 --> 00:09:44,480
Just like Dodge City.

197
00:09:44,790 --> 00:09:46,130
We have our reasons.

198
00:09:46,220 --> 00:09:47,170
Makes sense.

199
00:09:47,330 --> 00:09:48,630
Strong on the outside.

200
00:09:48,640 --> 00:09:49,690
Safe on the inside.

201
00:10:15,540 --> 00:10:17,830
Major, you're not gonna believe this.

202
00:10:18,040 --> 00:10:19,790
Three of Jacob's flock are back.

203
00:10:19,850 --> 00:10:20,860
Major Williams?

204
00:10:20,950 --> 00:10:22,000
We'd like to come back.

205
00:10:22,270 --> 00:10:23,610
We were wrong to leave.

206
00:10:23,610 --> 00:10:26,220
Jacob turned out to be just some crazy cult leader.

207
00:10:26,220 --> 00:10:27,430
We brought food.

208
00:10:28,480 --> 00:10:29,590
What do you want us to do?

209
00:10:30,910 --> 00:10:33,000
If they're clean, let 'em back in.

210
00:10:33,090 --> 00:10:36,120
Probably won't be the last of his sheep to wander back.

211
00:11:06,920 --> 00:11:08,990
I feel so much lighter without that damn hammer.

212
00:11:09,150 --> 00:11:11,210
Yeah, I feel naked, and not in a good way.

213
00:11:11,790 --> 00:11:13,740
When we started out, everyone was armed.

214
00:11:13,990 --> 00:11:17,040
Then one day a guy decided to shoot his wife's boyfriend.

215
00:11:17,610 --> 00:11:19,560
He turned, and we lost five people.

216
00:11:19,820 --> 00:11:20,920
So we made a rule.

217
00:11:21,270 --> 00:11:22,960
Only guards could carry inside.

218
00:11:23,810 --> 00:11:27,610
Then a trading group came in. Took a gun off a guard.

219
00:11:27,880 --> 00:11:31,160
Seven dead that time. We were lucky it wasn't worse.

220
00:11:31,690 --> 00:11:34,230
We have a strong perimeter. Never been breached.

221
00:11:34,310 --> 00:11:35,740
All our problems happened inside.

222
00:11:35,740 --> 00:11:37,230
So we removed the threats.

223
00:11:37,950 --> 00:11:40,270
No weapons inside the walls, period.

224
00:11:40,420 --> 00:11:42,250
It's a better way to live. Safer.

225
00:11:42,490 --> 00:11:44,610
Being armed all the time has an effect on people.

226
00:11:44,860 --> 00:11:47,400
Maybe I'm naive, but this gives me hope.

227
00:11:47,690 --> 00:11:49,060
Is this a zombie cage?

228
00:11:49,480 --> 00:11:51,170
Doesn't seem much use these days.

229
00:11:51,680 --> 00:11:53,810
We patrol the surrounding area for Zs twice a day,

230
00:11:53,810 --> 00:11:55,210
so they aren't really a problem.

231
00:11:55,700 --> 00:11:57,480
It's the people we have to worry about.

232
00:11:57,990 --> 00:11:59,360
Since going weapon-free,

233
00:11:59,360 --> 00:12:01,480
we've gone over a year without a fatality.

234
00:12:01,710 --> 00:12:04,210
Think about that. You've been out in the world.

235
00:12:04,320 --> 00:12:06,790
How many deaths have you seen in the last year?

236
00:12:07,420 --> 00:12:08,610
Enough for a lifetime.

237
00:12:08,720 --> 00:12:12,640
What if someone, you know, dies of natural causes?

238
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:15,400
Sure, that could happen.

239
00:12:16,790 --> 00:12:18,770
All the doors and gates close automatically,

240
00:12:18,770 --> 00:12:21,650
sealing off each section of the compound. Like on a submarine.

241
00:12:21,870 --> 00:12:23,470
Can't be opened by Zs.

242
00:12:23,470 --> 00:12:25,440
Everything's been zombie-proofed.

243
00:12:25,810 --> 00:12:27,350
You ever hear of the Titanic?

244
00:12:27,880 --> 00:12:30,450
You're welcome to wait outside in your vehicle.

245
00:12:31,010 --> 00:12:34,160
You'll have to forgive my friend. He's been through a lot.

246
00:12:34,190 --> 00:12:35,510
We all have.

247
00:12:35,510 --> 00:12:38,340
Nothing's perfect, but this is as close as it gets.

248
00:12:38,470 --> 00:12:39,940
After a while, most people find

249
00:12:39,940 --> 00:12:41,520
they can actually sleep through the night.

250
00:12:41,960 --> 00:12:43,870
Really? I can't imagine that.

251
00:12:44,960 --> 00:12:47,050
We grow all our own fruits and vegetables.

252
00:12:47,210 --> 00:12:49,970
The scraps and our waste all go into a biomass generator.

253
00:12:50,450 --> 00:12:53,010
We're up to four hours of electricity a day.

254
00:12:53,340 --> 00:12:55,520
Really? That's cool.

255
00:12:57,860 --> 00:12:59,170
What's their story?

256
00:12:59,470 --> 00:13:02,420
We had a little trouble a while back with a preacher we took in.

257
00:13:02,520 --> 00:13:04,030
He drank his own Kool-Aid.

258
00:13:04,030 --> 00:13:06,790
Decided the Zompocalypse was actually The Second Coming

259
00:13:06,790 --> 00:13:09,270
and we needed to save the Zs, not kill them.

260
00:13:09,420 --> 00:13:12,940
Calls them "The Resurrected." Real whack-job.

261
00:13:13,250 --> 00:13:14,650
I'm not an expert on the Bible,

262
00:13:14,650 --> 00:13:17,400
but I'm pretty sure there's nothing in there about zombies.

263
00:13:17,400 --> 00:13:19,450
We had to kick him out, along with his followers.

264
00:13:19,640 --> 00:13:23,030
I've seen this kind of thing before. Crazy spreads fast.

265
00:13:23,030 --> 00:13:24,810
So why would you let them back in?

266
00:13:24,810 --> 00:13:26,750
They all had family still here.

267
00:13:27,010 --> 00:13:28,410
I knew once they were out a while,

268
00:13:28,410 --> 00:13:30,800
they'd get hungry or scared and some would come back.

269
00:13:30,800 --> 00:13:32,920
Like clockwork these three turned up today.

270
00:13:33,660 --> 00:13:34,900
Not true believers, huh?

271
00:13:35,200 --> 00:13:37,510
Hard to believe on an empty stomach.

272
00:13:38,080 --> 00:13:40,380
Speaking of which, let's get you people something to eat.

273
00:13:40,380 --> 00:13:42,890
First meal is on me. The rest you trade for.

274
00:13:42,890 --> 00:13:45,120
No meat of course. Hope you're vegetarian.

275
00:13:45,420 --> 00:13:46,190
Oh yeah.

276
00:13:48,810 --> 00:13:51,280
We're headed to a CDC lab in California.

277
00:13:51,710 --> 00:13:53,770
You're never gonna make it to California.

278
00:13:53,920 --> 00:13:55,030
Yeah, that's what I've been told.

279
00:13:55,030 --> 00:13:56,850
No, seriously.

280
00:13:57,250 --> 00:13:59,730
The Zs are swarming out west. Millions of them.

281
00:13:59,730 --> 00:14:01,440
Been hearing about it second and third hand.

282
00:14:01,760 --> 00:14:03,020
Nothing left to eat in the city,

283
00:14:03,020 --> 00:14:05,360
so they're pouring into open country, forming mega herds.

284
00:14:05,360 --> 00:14:08,070
Rumor has it the whole west coast is a no-go zone.

285
00:14:08,370 --> 00:14:09,700
Well we still got to try.

286
00:14:10,120 --> 00:14:11,010
The guy's a pain in the ass,

287
00:14:11,110 --> 00:14:12,610
but he's our only chance for a cure.

288
00:14:12,610 --> 00:14:14,670
Getting yourself killed won't cure anything.

289
00:14:14,790 --> 00:14:16,010
