296
00:14:27,820 --> 00:14:31,880
I don't know. I've seen so much hope come to nothing.

297
00:14:32,790 --> 00:14:34,140
This is the first thing I've been a part of

298
00:14:34,140 --> 00:14:35,370
that might actually work.

299
00:14:35,570 --> 00:14:37,220
These folks rely on me.

300
00:14:38,600 --> 00:14:39,370
I know.

301
00:14:40,160 --> 00:14:41,020
I get it.

302
00:14:43,560 --> 00:14:45,750
I've got a spare room two or three of you can use.

303
00:14:45,750 --> 00:14:48,040
The rest can grab a bunk in the community room.

304
00:14:52,950 --> 00:14:54,430
Let me think about what you said.

305
00:14:54,830 --> 00:14:58,310
We'll talk more tomorrow. In the meantime, get some rest.

306
00:14:58,380 --> 00:14:59,090
Thanks.

307
00:14:59,370 --> 00:15:00,150
Thank you.

308
00:15:21,940 --> 00:15:24,920
Dude. Dude, slow down. They're not gonna take it from you.

309
00:15:25,820 --> 00:15:26,540
So...

310
00:15:27,610 --> 00:15:29,700
We got the lowdown on the sleeping situation.

311
00:15:29,870 --> 00:15:32,060
There's a room that two or three of us can share,

312
00:15:32,060 --> 00:15:33,260
and there's a communal bunk.

313
00:15:33,260 --> 00:15:34,370
Dibs on the room.

314
00:15:35,880 --> 00:15:39,410
What? Be less risk of anyone figuring out who I am.

315
00:15:41,720 --> 00:15:43,630
I think we should give it to those two.

316
00:15:47,390 --> 00:15:49,020
What, no, no, no. We're not a...

317
00:15:51,370 --> 00:15:52,970
Yeah, you guys take it.

318
00:15:52,970 --> 00:15:53,570
Yeah.

319
00:15:53,730 --> 00:15:55,120
Is it that obvious?

320
00:15:56,560 --> 00:15:57,380
Well...

321
00:15:58,920 --> 00:16:00,240
If we're gonna do the time,

322
00:16:00,930 --> 00:16:02,220
we may as well do the crime.

323
00:16:12,710 --> 00:16:14,300
- Are you serious? - Yes.

324
00:16:51,270 --> 00:16:52,960
It's not exactly what I was...

325
00:16:55,260 --> 00:16:56,460
It's perfect.

326
00:17:01,440 --> 00:17:02,590
Roberta, ummm...

327
00:17:02,990 --> 00:17:03,680
Yeah?

328
00:17:07,390 --> 00:17:08,110
I mean, come on.

329
00:17:08,110 --> 00:17:11,150
This room, it's like you know here's the bed.

330
00:17:12,660 --> 00:17:14,070
It's...

331
00:17:16,620 --> 00:17:17,570
cozy.

332
00:17:17,890 --> 00:17:18,760
Cozy.

333
00:17:22,270 --> 00:17:23,000
Yeah.

334
00:17:24,080 --> 00:17:25,410
I don't know what to say.

335
00:17:26,790 --> 00:17:28,090
Don't say anything.

336
00:17:49,460 --> 00:17:51,710
Hey, ummm, I don't have any...

337
00:17:52,220 --> 00:17:53,810
We'll think of something.

338
00:17:57,370 --> 00:17:58,890
I went to Catholic school.

339
00:17:59,610 --> 00:18:00,360
Oh.

340
00:18:02,600 --> 00:18:03,340
Chair.

341
00:18:03,430 --> 00:18:04,130
All right.

342
00:18:10,170 --> 00:18:11,680
What are you worried about the nuns?

343
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:14,040
Never know.

344
00:18:40,730 --> 00:18:43,750
For indeed we have had good news preached to us,

345
00:18:44,670 --> 00:18:46,430
just as the unbelievers.

346
00:18:47,590 --> 00:18:49,540
But the word they heard did not profit them,

347
00:18:49,540 --> 00:18:51,610
for their hearts were closed to the truth.

348
00:18:52,510 --> 00:18:53,580
So then we

349
00:18:54,490 --> 00:18:56,270
shall open their eyes.

350
00:19:02,320 --> 00:19:03,800
That fella seems pretty popular

351
00:19:03,800 --> 00:19:05,750
for a guy who just got kicked out of here.

352
00:19:06,180 --> 00:19:07,860
It was a lot harder than we expected it.

353
00:19:08,750 --> 00:19:10,320
Thought we'd be better off back here.

354
00:19:11,200 --> 00:19:13,870
Lucky for you the Major was willing to take you in again.

355
00:19:14,980 --> 00:19:17,290
Yes, it was lucky for us all.

356
00:19:27,640 --> 00:19:29,640
Hey, Luke. Glad to see you back, man.

357
00:19:30,030 --> 00:19:32,280
I knew you were too smart to fall for that Jacob clown.

358
00:19:32,410 --> 00:19:32,950
Yeah.

359
00:19:32,950 --> 00:19:34,720
It wasn't at all what I thought it was gonna be.

360
00:19:34,870 --> 00:19:35,770
Glad to be back.

361
00:19:36,470 --> 00:19:39,180
I think I left some meds in my ammo bag.

362
00:19:39,420 --> 00:19:40,510
Do you mind checking for me?

363
00:19:40,510 --> 00:19:41,500
Sure, hang on.

364
00:20:10,300 --> 00:20:11,800
Hey, are you all right?

365
00:20:22,290 --> 00:20:24,080
Listen to me, all of you,

366
00:20:24,520 --> 00:20:26,040
